        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Chemistry Context\n\nThe Cu²⁺–EDTA system is one of the most extensively studied metal–chelate equilibria, with nearly 50 independent literature sources compiled in SRD-46 spanning from Schwarzenbach's pioneering 1949 work through the late 1990s. The Brunetti, Nancollas & Smith (1969) study is a well-regarded calorimetric/potentiometric investigation that provided both stability constants and thermodynamic parameters (ΔH, ΔS) for several metal–EDTA complexes. Their measurement yielded the largest reported value for the simple 1:1 Cu²⁺–EDTA formation equilibrium in the database.\n\n*Source: NIST Standard Reference Database 46 (Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes).*",
